{{Infobox university |name = Academy of Music and Drama |native_name = Högskolan för scen och musik |native_name_lang = sv |former_name = |type = [[Music school]], [[Drama school]] |affiliations = [[University of Gothenburg]] |parent = [[University of Gothenburg]] |image_name = File:GU - Artisten.JPG |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = Artisten building |established = {{Start date|2005}} |closed = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} --> |city = [[Gothenburg]] |country = [[Sweden]] |coor = |dean = |academic_staff = |administrative_staff = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |motto = |motto_lang = |motto_eng = |website = {{URL|www.hsm.gu.se}} |logo = }}
The '''Academy of Music and Drama''' ([[Swedish language|Swedish]]: ''Högskolan för scen och musik'', abbreviated HSM) at the [[University of Gothenburg]] is a school for music, composition, opera singing, music staging, teaching of music and creative subjects in [[Gothenburg]]. It belongs to the Faculty of Fine, Applied and Performing Arts.
It was started in 2005.<ref>http://www.hsm.gu.se/english/about-us/academy-history/?languageId=100001&disableRedirect=true&returnUrl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hsm.gu.se%2Fom-institutionen%2Fhistorik%2F</ref> as a merger of the former departments of music, theater and opera at the university.
The main campus building is Artisten in Gothenburg.
The school also acts as a training center for orchestral music. The programme is called the Swedish National Orchestra Academy (SNOA) and was started by the then head Ingemar Henningsson after preparatory work with the [[Gothenburg Symphony Orchestra]] (Göteborgs Symfoniker). The two-year program organizes about 8 or 9 orchestral projects per academic year.
